  {
    "username": "emollick",
    "nickname": "Ethan Mollick",
    "text": "As this post points out, contrary to what many say, the US government could absolutely effectively ban open weights models. That doesn’t mean you won’t be able to download the weights &amp; run them, but they can ensure that no US company would use or provide access or host them",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/emollick/status/2070308786032578766",
    "time": "2026-06-26 08:50",
    "created_at": "Fri Jun 26 00:50:53 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2070308786032578766",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "emollick",
    "nickname": "Ethan Mollick",
    "text": "The point is that AI regulation will not somehow ignore open source as a loophole.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/emollick/status/2070310368950251891",
    "time": "2026-06-26 08:57",
    "created_at": "Fri Jun 26 00:57:11 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2070310368950251891",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "emollick",
    "nickname": "Ethan Mollick",
    "text": "I feel like on X all you hear about is elaborate plans by firms to build their own AI stacks but in my experience companies are full of people who want access to Claude or ChatGPT and are pressuring their purchasing staff to get licenses so they can just use the tools they know.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/emollick/status/2070324736052084780",
    "time": "2026-06-26 09:54",
    "created_at": "Fri Jun 26 01:54:16 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2070324736052084780",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "emollick",
    "nickname": "Ethan Mollick",
    "text": "Most companies are not even thinking about giving every employee a fine-tuned self-hosted version of GLM that they need to update and keep harnessed and build connectors for.\n\nThere are lots of places where roll-your-own AI stacks make sense, but end users want name brands.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/emollick/status/2070325481975484784",
    "time": "2026-06-26 09:57",
    "created_at": "Fri Jun 26 01:57:14 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2070325481975484784",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
